data.name: Label5.Text
data.value: Menu options: 1. "Exit" quits the program. "Patterns" and "Candles" selects chart patterns or candlesticks you wish to find. "Fib" is to find Fibonacci retraces and extensions. Select a stock symbol (2) to ungray. "File Format" is for advanced users. Refer to http://thepatternsite.com/PatternzNew.html#PZTourFF for more information. "Manual Score" is a manual scoring system (the automated version is Score (5)). "Rel Strength" provides a comparison of stock vs stock to find the best performers. "Splits/Divs" tell if a stock has split or issued a dividend. "Fix Split" repairs the data after a split.

data.name: Label6.Text
data.value: 5. "Browse Portfolio Location" finds the location where you place your stock files/symbols shown in 2. "Indicator" runs the chart pattern indicator. "Score" helps select chart patterns that outperform. "Select All" highlights all files shown in 2. "Chart" graphs the stock and finds patterns. "List" runs through the files, looking for patterns and shows the results in a table. Use "Update" to update your data files or add new symbols to the list at 2.
